        "body": "<p>Another way of implementing this is to have cascade on <code>@ManyToMany<\/code> relationship.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Account {\n  @Id\n  private Long id;\n  [..]\n  @ManyToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n  @JoinTable(name = \"account_client\",\n    joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = \"account_id\"),\n    inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = \"client_id\"))\n  private List&lt;Client&gt; clients;\n}\n\npublic class Client {\n  @Id\n  private Long id;\n  [..]\n  @ManyToMany(mappedBy = \"clients\", cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n  private List&lt;Client&gt; accounts;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and on save you would have the list of accounts which would have a list of clients and the cascade will take care of persists, updates, deletes.<\/p>\n",
